<Layout
	title="About TechFrontier"
	description="Our methodology and thesis"
	pubDate={new Date('2026-02-28')}
>
	<p>
		<strong>TechFrontier</strong> is an automated intelligence briefing designed to identify high-signal technical breakthroughs before they reach mainstream commercial adoption.
	</p>
	<p>
		By programmatically scanning developer hubs (such as HackerNews, GitHub) and leveraging AI models for semantic synthesis, we separate the foundational architectural shifts from the noise. Our focus is squarely on engineering execution, open-source validation, and early-stage capital efficiency.
	</p>
	<h3>Methodology</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Automated Ingestion</strong>: Continuous polling of top-tier developer signals.</li>
		<li><strong>Semantic Filtering</strong>: Leveraging LLMs to discard marketing fluff and focus on underlying technical specs.</li>
		<li><strong>Zero-Noise Delivery</strong>: A minimalist reading experience without distractions.</li>
	</ul>
</Layout>
